    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look poised for high offensive output today, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (81.77). **Gunnar Henderson** holds the slate\u2019s top efficiency score, benefiting from a high-leadoff spot, a favorable matchup against Wacha, and wind patterns blowing out that provide a +5% boost to his base projection. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** is in a prime spot against Tyler Mahle; despite the lineup pending, his elite xwOBA metrics and the same wind-out advantage make him a foundational piece for our daily production. **Jackson Merrill** also presents excellent value (75.10), as he draws a significant +14% park factor boost and a healthy +17% bump due to the favorable SP matchup against Sugano.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved keeping **Marcell Ozuna** on the bench despite his solid 60.81 score. He came within a hair of cracking the starting lineup, but the optimizer prioritized the higher ceiling of players like **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Luis Robert Jr.**, who benefit more from specific platoon advantages or order placement. **Jacob Wilson** and **Heliot Ramos** carry the most risk today, with **Jacob Wilson** facing the elite arm of Gilbert and **Heliot Ramos** tasked with battling Shohei Ohtani. While **Heliot Ramos** benefits from the wind, his low score (40.72) is heavily suppressed by the SP\u2019s dominance, pushing him right to the edge of our efficiency floor. We will be monitoring the pending lineups for **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, and **Heliot Ramos** closely; any downward shift in their batting order could necessitate a late swap to optimize our 5x5 Roto trajectory.",
